        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Bah mages just destroyed alot of good will towards their class. The irony is people don't realise how useful dire charm is to the classes that actually use the ability.</P><P>Solo<BR>Normal variable duration charms allow more powerful mobs to be killed at a faster rate and you get to kill your pet for exp when it gets low health. This is true for necros,chanters and druids. (remember the exp penalty for not getting half damage and the difficulty of keeping the pet alive)</P><P>Raid<BR>There are two zones where and enchanter could use a dire charmed pet. Keal and icewall keep. None where a druid or necro could use one.</P><P>Group<BR>This is the only place where dire charm makes a difference. Normal random duration charms are far more powerful but require that the charmer always be at the keyboard and spend mana+health(sometimes a little health,sometimes alot) on the recharms. The enchanter using direcharm can slow/stun/mez everything and still have pet. The necro can heal/do damage and still have pet. The druid can nuke/spot heal and still have pet. Becuase verant really doesn't like soloing and likes people playing groups I doubt that they will nerf this skill.</P><P>silfe xev</P><P><BR>silfe xev<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
