ith this issue because our lifetaps couldn't land on these mobs stifling the whole essence of how we deal damage/mana.</P><P><BR>For one of the above posters that claims that our pet nerfs was because of warriors complaining about our pets being overpowered, and had nothing to do with mage pets.  Let me sum up how this all went.</P><P>1. Warriors complained that Necro pets were overpowered.</P><P>2. VI nerfs Necro pets down to where they "should" be.</P><P>3. In return, Mages brought it to VI's attention that even after being nerfed, necro pets were still more powerful than current mage pets.</P><P>4. Mage pets were increased in HP's/Level to make them more balanced as to where the "masters of summoning" should be (yes, VI also coined that phrase), and shortly after this, dual weilding of mage pets was fixed.</P><P>5. After Dual Weild was fixed, VI noticed that they went overboard on buffing mage pets and put in the dagger nerf to tone them back down to where they should be.</P><P>6. This dagger nerf affected ALL pet classes due to coding at the time and hurt necro pets even further after they were considered balanced.</P><P>As a bone, Necro pets were given a Lifetap proc to help level them back up (which still to this day is broken, and did not make up the difference from where out pets were considered balanced)</P><P><BR>Looking back over this, our pets were nerfed as a "side affect" of balancing mage pets, and to this day, our pets are still underpowered due to these nerfs.</P><P><BR>Ok, so this post is longer than it should be.</P><P><BR>Kiluudar Ravenwind  60 Warlock,  Fennin Ro,   T'kagi Ro<BR><br><BR><img src="http://www.users.qwest.net/~hmg9/images/Usfla.gif"" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
